    <exercises>
        <exercise>
            <statement>
            <p>
                The income tax rates of a certain year were shown in the table below:
            </p>
            <tabular left="medium" right="medium" top="medium" bottom="medium">
                            <row header="yes">
                                <cell>Monthly taxable</cell>
                                <cell>Tax rate <m>(\%)</m> </cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell><m>0 \;\text{to} \; 9,680 </m></cell>
                                <cell><m>10</m></cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell><m>9,681 \;\text{to} \; 18,800</m></cell>
                                <cell><m>15</m></cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell><m>18,801 \;\text{to} \; 27,920</m></cell>
                                <cell><m>20</m></cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell><m>27,921 \;\text{to} \; 37,040</m></cell>
                                <cell><m>25</m></cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell><m>37,041 \;\text{and above} </m></cell>
                                <cell><m>30</m></cell>
                            </row>
            </tabular>
            <p>
                In that year, Jacob's monthly earnings were as follows:
            </p>
            <p>
                <md>
                    <mrow> \text{Basic salary} \; \amp = \; \text{Ksh}\; 28,600 </mrow>
                    <mrow> \text{House allowance} \; \amp = \; \text{Ksh}\; 15,000 </mrow>
                    <mrow> \text{Medical allowance} \; \amp = \; \text{Ksh}\; 3,200 </mrow>
                    <mrow> \text{Transport allowance} \; \amp = \; \text{Ksh}\; 540 </mrow>
                </md>
            </p>
            <p>
                Jacob was entitled to a monthly tax relief of Ksh <m> 1,056</m>
            </p>
            <p>
                <ol marker="(a)">
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Calculate the tax charge on Jacob's monthly earnings.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Apart from income tax, the following monthly deductions were made; a health insurance fund of Ksh <m>500</m>, Education insurance of Ksh <m> 1,200</m>, and <m> 2 \%</m> of his basic salary for widows and children pension scheme. Calculate Jacob's monthly net income from his employment.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
            <p>
                <ol marker="(a)">
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            <m> \text{Ksh} \; 8, 474 </m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            <m> \text{Ksh} \; 36,594 </m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>
        </answer>      
        </exercise>    
        <exercise>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    The table below shows the income tax rates of a certain year.
                </p>
                <tabular left="medium" right="medium" top="medium" bottom="medium">
                            <row header="yes">
                                <cell>Monthly income in Kenyan shillings (Ksh)</cell>
                                <cell>Tax rate in each shilling </cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell><m>0 - 10,164 </m></cell>
                                <cell><m>10 \%</m></cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell><m>10,165 - 19,740</m></cell>
                                <cell><m>15 \%</m></cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell><m>19,741 - 29,316</m></cell>
                                <cell><m>20 \%</m></cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell><m>29,317 - 38,892</m></cell>
                                <cell><m>25 \%</m></cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell><m>\text{Over} \; 38,892 </m></cell>
                                <cell><m>30 \%</m></cell>
                            </row>
                </tabular>
                <p>
                    A tax relief of Ksh <m>1,162</m> per month was allowed. In a certain month, of that year, Obiero's taxable income in the fifth band was Ksh <m> 2,108</m>.
                </p>
                <p>
                    <ol marker="(a)">
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Calculate:
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                <ol marker="(i)">
                                    <li>
                                        <p>
                                            Obiero's taxable income in that month.
                                        </p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <p>
                                            The tax payable by Obiero in than month.
                                        </p>
                                    </li>
                                </ol>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Obiero's income include a house allowance of Ksh <m> 15,000</m> per month. Obiero contributed <m> 5\%</m> of the basic salary to a co-operative society. Calculate the employees net pay for that month.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </statement>
            <answer>
                <p>
                    <ol marker="(a)">
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                <ol marker="(i)">
                                    <li>
                                        <p>
                                            Ksh <m> 41,000</m>
                                        </p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <p>
                                            Ksh <m> 6,232.40</m>
                                        </p>
                                    </li>
                                </ol>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Ksh <m> 33,467.60</m>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </answer>
        </exercise>  
        <exercise>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    In June of ertain year, Nicholus basic salary was Ksh <m>17,000</m>. Nicholus was also paid a house allowance of Ksh <m>6,000</m>, a commuter allowance of Ksh <m>2,500</m>, and a medical allowance of Ksh <m>1,800</m>. In JUly of that year, Nicholas's basic salary was raised by <m>2 \%</m>. 
                </p>
                <p>
                    <ol marker="(a)">
                        <li>
                            <p>
                               Calculate Nicholas's: 
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                <ol marker="(i)">
                                    <li>
                                        <p>
                                           Nicholas basic salary in July. 
                                        </p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <p>
                                            Total taxable income in July of that year. 
                                        </p>
                                    </li>
                                </ol>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                During that year, the taxable income Tax Rates were as shown in the table below:
                            </p>
                            <tabular left="medium" right="medium" top="medium" bottom="medium">
                                <row header="yes">
                                    <cell>Monthly taxable income (Ksh) </cell>
                                    <cell>Percentage rate of tax per shilling</cell>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <cell>Up to <m>9,680</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>10</m></cell>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <cell>From <m>9,681</m> to <m>18,800</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>15</m></cell>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <cell>From <m>18,801</m> to <m>27,920</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>20</m></cell>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <cell>From <m>27,921</m> to <m>37,040</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>25</m></cell>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <cell>From <m>37,041</m> and above</cell>
                                    <cell><m>30</m></cell>
                                </row>
                            </tabular>
                            <p>
                                Given that the monthly personal relief was Ksh <m>1,056</m>, Calculate the net tax paid by the employee.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </statement>
            <answer>
                <p>
                    <ol marker="(a)">
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                <ol marker="(i)">
                                    <li>
                                        <p>
                                            Ksh <m>17,340</m>
                                        </p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <p>
                                            Ksh <m>27,640</m>
                                        </p>
                                    </li>
                                </ol>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Ksh <m>3,048</m>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </answer>
        </exercise>  
    </exercises>

    <axiom component="lesson-plan">
        <title>Differentiation Strategies</title>

        <table>
            <title>Differentiation Matrix for Progressive Income Tax</title>
            <tabular halign="left" top="medium" bottom="medium" left="medium" right="medium">
                <row header="yes" bottom="minor">
                    <cell>Learner Group</cell>
                    <cell>Strategy &amp; Learning Experience</cell>
                </row>

                <row bottom="minor">
                    <cell><alert>Struggling Learners (Support)</alert></cell>
                    <cell>
                        <p>
                            Provide targeted assistance isolating basic single-band tax exercises before jumping into multi-layered progressive structures. Use pre-rendered visual flowcharts tracking gross earnings down to net income.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Worksheets include clear structural boundaries for tax calculations. Provide scaffolds showing how to partition money within the first active band boundary (e.g., matching the initial threshold limit) before checking higher brackets.
                        </p>
                    </cell>
                </row>

                <row bottom="minor">
                    <cell><alert>On-Level Learners (Core)</alert></cell>
                    <cell>
                        <p>
                            Learners practice breaking salaries into sequential portions, reading complex data matrices, mapping currencies, and using multiple compound slabs to execute PAYE scenarios.
                        </p>
                        
                    </cell>
                </row>

                <row>
                    <cell><alert>Advanced Learners (Challenge)</alert></cell>
                    <cell>
                        <p>
                            Extend problems to complex backward calculations, where learners determine original basic salaries or total gross pay starting from a given net take-home pay and tax framework.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Learners explore and analyze how sudden modifications to state tax brackets or relief limits impact distinct economic demographics. They construct contextual commercial application tasks, design progressive tax matrices, and lead peer troubleshooting workshops.
                        </p>
                    </cell>
                </row>
            </tabular>
        </table>

        <paragraphs>
            <title>Teacher Execution Guidance</title>
            <ol>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        <alert>Classroom Layout:</alert> Seat struggling learners together near the front of the room. This allows you to check their first-band calculations quickly while core and advanced groups work independently on multi-slab calculations and backward-mapping challenges.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        <alert>Strategic Peer Mentoring:</alert> Pair on-level learners who finish early with support groups as peer consultants. Having them explain how to calculate tax on an overflow balance helps solidify their own mathematical reasoning.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        <alert>Extension Prompts:</alert> Challenge advanced learners by asking: <em>"If a worker receives an extra Ksh 5,000 bonus that pushes them into the highest tax bracket, how does their net bonus compare to a worker whose bonus stays in a lower bracket?"</em> This helps connect algebraic computations to real-world economic logic.
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </paragraphs>
    </axiom>

